description:
Cemetery: South
Large square shaft. 2.90 x 2.90 m. depth 9 m. top well bricked
Stele in rubbish above shaft.
Also few bl. gl. beads, fragments & a broken Ushabti.
Fragts. of bl. gl. bowl & lid
Small cylindrical beads
Pair of horns, goat or ram.
Fragts. of v. late pottery.
Half a limestone figure, rough work, female with wig
The grave is clearly late & later still the shaft was filled up with fragments of mummies.
OVER.
inputBy: Michael George Adams; Amanda Ford Spora; Denis Antoine
